long_desc.thetext:
As stated in MDC [1], Firefox 3.1 will be out as 3.5. That means that qooxdoo Bugzilla also needs some love in accordance. :-)


The intuitive steps should be fairly simple (I'm not a Bugzilla expert, though this list of actions sounds reasonable):
1. Move all "Firefox 3.1" platform bugs [2] to "Firefox 3.5";
2. Create platform "Firefox 3.6";
3. Move all "Firefox 3.2" platform bugs [3] (none as of this writing) to "Firefox 3.6";
4. Remove platforms "Firefox 3.1" and "Firefox 3.2";

Steps 1 and 3 can be done by anyone with bug edit privileges (I'll try to do step 1 ASAP, step 3 is currently not needed), but the other remaining steps must be done by someone with (Bugzilla) administration privileges. ;-)

The Bugzilla queries [2] [3] can also be used as a quick way to check for hanging bugs before actually removing the platform entries (although I bet Bugzilla complains if something would break from such a change). :-)

[1] https://developer.mozilla.org/devnews/index.php/2009/03/06/shiretoko-to-be-named-firefox-35/
[2] http://bugzilla.qooxdoo.org/buglist.cgi?query_format=advanced&rep_platform=Firefox+3.1
[3] http://bugzilla.qooxdoo.org/buglist.cgi?query_format=advanced&rep_platform=Firefox+3.2

